---
import TalleyPage from '../../../components/talley-wealth/TalleyPage.astro';
---

<TalleyPage
  title="About Talley Wealth | Independent Financial Planning, Johnson City TN"
  description="David Talley, CFP®, ChFC®, EA. An independent fee-based planning firm in Johnson City, Tennessee, built around coordinated planning, investments, and tax strategy."
  heroTransparent
  ogImage="/brands/talley-wealth/david-talley.webp"
>
  <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
    <div class="section-container grid min-h-[70vh] items-center gap-12 py-20 pt-32 sm:pt-40 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">About Talley Wealth</p>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold leading-tight md:text-4xl lg:text-6xl">About the firm</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-white/80 md:text-lg">
          Talley Wealth is a small, independent, fee-based planning firm in Johnson City, Tennessee. I started it because I wanted to do this work a particular way: plan first, run the investments to fit the plan, and use tax strategy as a year-round lever. Most of the industry runs the other way around.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end" data-reveal="right">
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 rotate-3 rounded-2xl bg-accent/20"></div>
          <div class="relative aspect-[3/4] w-72 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl shadow-elegant-xl md:w-80 lg:w-96">
            <img decoding="async" src="/brands/talley-wealth/david-talley.webp" alt="David Talley, CFP®, ChFC®, EA" class="h-full w-full object-cover" loading="eager" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-card">
    <div class="section-container py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary md:text-4xl">Why I built the firm this way</h2>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          <p>
            I spent the early part of my career watching successful people arrive at the most important financial chapter of their lives without the kind of coordinated planning they had earned. They had done the saving. They had made the right calls for thirty years. And then they reached retirement, or a business sale, or an inheritance, and the three pieces that mattered most, the plan, the investments, and the taxes, were being handled by three different people who never talked to each other. I built Talley Wealth to do those three things together, on purpose, in the right order.
          </p>
          <p>
            That's the whole thesis. The plan comes first. The investments calibrate to it. Tax strategy runs through it as a year-round lever, not as something to react to in April. It sounds obvious when you say it. It's also genuinely rare.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="section-container py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary md:text-4xl">Who's on the team</h2>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          <p>
            It's two of us. I lead the client work. Stephenee Carberry, our Practice Manager, keeps everything running between sessions, handles the operational side of every engagement, and is usually the first person you'll talk to after you book the Explore Call. We're small on purpose. The work doesn't scale by adding more advisors; it scales by being careful about how many engagements I take on at once.
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="/about/meet-david-talley" class="font-semibold text-accent hover:underline">Read more about my background.</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-card">
    <div class="section-container py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary md:text-4xl">Independence and how we get paid</h2>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          <p>
            Talley Wealth is independent. We aren't owned by a broker-dealer, a bank, or an insurance company. We don't sell products. The only way we make money is the fee a client pays directly. That alignment isn't a marketing claim, it's the structural reason we can give the advice we give. The full fee structure is on the <a href="/pricing" class="font-semibold text-accent hover:underline">pricing page</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="section-container py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-3xl text-center" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Continue exploring</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary md:text-4xl">Where the story connects to the work.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-5xl gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
        <a href="/about/meet-david-talley" class="group rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-elegant transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-elegant-lg">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary transition group-hover:text-accent">Meet David</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Background, credentials, local roots, and the way David thinks about the work.</p>
          <span class="mt-5 inline-flex text-sm font-bold text-accent">Read more <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;-&gt;</span></span>
        </a>
        <a href="/how-we-work/keystone-method" class="group rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-elegant transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-elegant-lg">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary transition group-hover:text-accent">The Keystone Method</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">See how the planning-first philosophy turns into a structured six-month engagement.</p>
          <span class="mt-5 inline-flex text-sm font-bold text-accent">Read more <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;-&gt;</span></span>
        </a>
        <a href="/pricing" class="group rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-elegant transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-elegant-lg">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary transition group-hover:text-accent">Pricing</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Review the flat planning fees and how ongoing advisory works after Keystone.</p>
          <span class="mt-5 inline-flex text-sm font-bold text-accent">Read more <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;-&gt;</span></span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-card">
    <div class="section-container py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          If any of this resonates with how you're thinking about the next chapter of your financial life, the next step is a 15-minute Explore Call. There's no prep needed and no pressure to move forward afterward.
        </p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="mt-10 inline-flex rounded-md bg-accent px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-accent-foreground shadow-elegant transition hover:brightness-95">Schedule an Explore Call</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</TalleyPage>
